\paragraph{\qol in the Matched Cohort}
Since the DBS target was chosen following a patient-specific approach, the lack of influence of the target on the \qol could be due to selection bias. Using propensity score matching, we created an STN subgroup, whose average baseline variables did not differ from the GPi cohort (Supplementary Table \ref{tab:tablmatched}). Comparing these two groups we did not see a significant difference in the postoperative PDQ--39 SI, with a tendency for the STN patients to have a better \qol one year after surgery (\Sexpr{match_diff_pdq} points on the PDQ--39 SI, p = \Sexpr{formatPval(p_matches)}).\\
Postural stability and the MMS outcome were important criteria for the target selection. In the matched group, the postural stability improved in the STN group (mean improvement \Sexpr{match_diff_stability_stn}) while the GPi group slightly worsened (mean improvement \Sexpr{match_diff_stability_gpi}, \Sexpr{match_diff_stability_p}). There was no difference in MMS outcome between the two targets.

